he perspective of distance gained by leaving fundamentalism, each story gives the reader a snapshot of what it is like to go through the experiences, thoughts, feelings, passions, and pains that, for many of the writers, are still raw. Explaining how their lives might continue after fundamentalism, these writers offer a spiritual lifeline for others who may be questioning their faith. Foreword by Thomas Moore, author of Care of the Soul and many other books.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian biography. 0aEx-church membersvBiography. 0aFundamentalism. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aLife Writing. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Fundamentalism.2bisacsh  aChristian faith.  aChristian fundamentalism.  aChristian living.  aChristian memoir.  aafter fundamentalism.  achurch as authority.  acrisis of faith.  aexvangelical.  afundamentalist church.  alearning about faith.  aleaving the church.  alosing faith.1 aBryant, Beverley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDann, G. Elijah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDann, G. Elijah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDixon, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrell, Margaret Steel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFieser, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLivingston, L.A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinaker, Leia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMolinari, Andrea Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRak, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https:/